        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "distinguishing features",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            161,
            575,
            322,
            592
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Pentagonal in shape, cushion-like body, often inflated when landed (as in photo), but slowly deflates with time out of water. Numerous papillae coat the aboral surface. Ventral smooth with fine lines.",
        "bbox": [
            161,
            592,
            489,
            664
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Colour",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            161,
            676,
            211,
            692
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Speckled brilliant orange aboral surface and pale cream smooth oral surface.",
        "bbox": [
            161,
            693,
            487,
            722
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Size",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            163,
            734,
            194,
            750
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Up to 160 mm diameter.",
        "bbox": [
            161,
            751,
            321,
            766
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "image",
        "img_path": "images/e74ee4b8c4c6a339abfe8f79af7a783a8bdb662295217a306c3b7483962ff05a.jpg",
        "image_caption": [],
        "image_footnote": [],
        "bbox": [
            509,
            322,
            833,
            551
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "distribution",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            509,
            575,
            596,
            590
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "West and South Coasts of South Africa; from 40 to 205+ m depth.",
        "bbox": [
            509,
            590,
            835,
            621
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Similar species",
        "text_level": 2,
        "bbox": [
            509,
            633,
            615,
            649
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Chondraster elattosis, but S. brachyactis inflates and is not as leathery.",
        "bbox": [
            509,
            650,
            835,
            680
        ],
        "page_idx": 2
    },
    {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "references",
